<subSubSection pageId="109" pageNumber="505" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="109.[115,1327,879,2017]" pageId="109" pageNumber="505">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[124,471,1746,1779]" pageId="109" pageNumber="505">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Least Concern on The IUCN Red List. From 1999 to 2006, attempts to find Negev White-toothed Shrewsfailed. Low rainfall may have caused a population drop; or the species may switch to deeper soil layers in dry times. Threats to the Negev White-toothed Shrew are unknown. The species has been found in five protected areas.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
